          <div class="hl">= Contribution ÷ Visibility</div>
          <br>
          <div>Adjusted SCOI</div>
          <div class="hl">= Raw SCOI × ERF</div>
          <br>
          <span class="result">CRIPFCnt Success<br>= Blind Success ± Net Structural Contribution</span>
        </div>
        <div class="eq-vars">
          <div class="eq-var"><div class="eq-var-name">SCOI</div><div class="eq-var-def">Structural Contribution Output Index</div></div>
          <div class="eq-var"><div class="eq-var-name">ERF</div><div class="eq-var-def">Environmental Resilience Factor</div></div>
          <div class="eq-var"><div class="eq-var-name">Visibility</div><div class="eq-var-def">Space occupied in others' awareness</div></div>
          <div class="eq-var"><div class="eq-var-name">Contribution</div><div class="eq-var-def">What you actually produce for others</div></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="eq-content reveal">
        <div class="section-label">The Numbers Behind It</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Not all success contributes. Not all contribution is seen.</h2>
        <p>The SCOI system makes the invisible measurable. An entity can have enormous visibility but minimal contribution - inflating its apparent success. Or extraordinary contribution that goes entirely unrecognised. The Adjusted SCOI corrects for the environment's difficulty, producing a fairer picture of where an individual or organisation truly stands.</p>
        <p style="font-size:0.9rem; color:rgba(255,255,255,0.55);">The Environmental Resilience Factor (ERF) accounts for operating context: economic instability, systemic inequality, geographic disadvantage. A high ERF acknowledges that the same output achieved in a harder environment represents greater structural contribution.</p>
        <a href="/scoi" class="btn btn-gold" style="margin-top:2rem; display:inline-block;">Run a SCOI Audit →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
